  "prompt": "What are some of the funniest YouTube videos?",
  "response": "Humor is quite subjective, so what might be funny to one person may not be to another. However, here are some popular YouTube videos and channels that are known for their comedic content and have garnered millions of views:\n\n1. **Ryan Higa (nigahiga)** - His \"How to be a Ninja\" and \"How to be Gangster\" series are classic parodies that showcase his humor and creativity.\n\n2. **David Dobrik** - Known for his vlogs, many of which feature hilarious pranks, surprises, and interactions with his friends (the \"Vlog Squad\").\n\n3. **Key & Peele** - Their sketches often incorporate clever social commentary and absurd situations. Notable ones include \"Substitute Teacher\" and \"East/West College Bowl.\"\n\n4. **Smosh** - This channel has a variety of humorous sketches, including the popular \"If _____ Were Real\" series.\n\n5. **CollegeHumor** - Their sketches cover various relatable topics, and videos like \"The World\u2019s Toughest Job\" provide a humorous take on everyday scenarios.\n\n6. **Funny Animal Videos** - Channels dedicated to funny animal compilations, like \"The Dodo\" or \"Funny Pet Videos,\" often provide light-hearted, hilarious content.\n\n7. **Julia Nunes** - Known for her comedic songs and humorous commentary on everyday life.\n\n8. **Conan O'Brien Needs A Friend** - While primarily a podcast, some episodes are available on YouTube and feature hilarious interviews with various celebrities.\n\n9. **John Cena vs. The Rock** - Various funny moments from wrestling matches have become memes and are compiled in various YouTube videos.\n\n10. **Mean Tweets (Jimmy Kimmel Live)** - Celebrities reading mean tweets about themselves is both funny and relatable.\n\nBe sure to check out specific videos or sketches from these creators for a good laugh!",
